OL,3,CWelsh rugby braced for radical shake-
OL,4,Cup as proposed cut to two teams
OL,5,Cconfirmed
OL,7,FReddin confirmed his preference is to
OL,8,Fhalve the number of professional clubs
OL,9,Fand establish a state-of-the-art
OL,10,Fnational campus, where the men's and
OL,11,Fwomen's teams of both clubs would
OL,12,Ftrain alongside a centralised academy.
OL,14,FCurrently, Wales has four professional
OL,15,Fsides: Cardiff Rugby, the Dragons in
OL,16,FNewport, the Ospreys in Swansea and
OL,17,Fthe Scarlets in Llanelli. It remains
OL,18,Funclear whether two of these teams
OL,19,Fwill survive, whether mergers will
OL,20,Ftake place, or if entirely new
OL,21,Fentities will be created.
